item.title: Apollos best friend, SnackMan was at work today!
item.description: I don't know much about SnackMan. I know he works for a local business that does concert and arena sound, and I once spoke to a colleague of his who told me that SnackMan lets his colleagues drop their dogs off at his station, almost like a doggy daycare. I also know that he gives a snack to every dog that walks past on this walkway that is allowed one from their owner. He must buy in bulk. Bottom line is: SnackMan loves dogs, and the dogs love SnackMan. The world needs more superheroes like him.

item.title: Although He Knew His Rights And The Law....
item.description: ....I believe this would have turned differently if the guy in the car was not also a cop. Edit: From my response to a comment. Protected Speech vs. Verbal Attacks Directed at Officers. Words alone—even profane, offensive, and insulting ones—directed at police generally won't be enough for criminal charges. These words are protected under the First Amendment. You can't threaten harm though. But be forewarned..they can still arrest you if they want to ruin you day, but you probably won't be convicted. There's a saying..."You can beat the rap but you can't be the ride. "
